comments: Duren (DET) slides his hand off Wagner's (ORL) off-arm after Wagner gathers, and the contact is marginal.
Ivey (DET) is already beginning to lose the ball on the attempted handoff before Suggs (ORL) reaches his hand toward it, and marginal contact occurs.
Duren (DET) extends his arms into Carter Jr.'s (ORL) body and dislodges him from his legally obtained position.
Thompson (DET) initiates the contact by wrapping his arms around Wagner (ORL) off-ball, which affects Wagner's FOM.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Wagner's (ORL) path and absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Cunningham (DET) releases from Suggs (ORL) at the end of the drive.
Suggs (ORL) legally contests Cunningham's (DET) jump shot attempt.
Cunningham (DET) keeps a resting hand as he moves alongside Wagner's (ORL) path during the shot attempt in the lane.
Suggs (ORL) reaches for the ball when slight contact occurs with Duren's (DET) arm, which does not affect his ability to control the rebound.
Harris (ORL) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Cunningham (DET) briefly in the backcourt.
Suggs (ORL) initiates the contact by extending his hand into Cunningham's (DET) front at the start of the drive, which affects his SQBR.

Carter Jr. (ORL) makes incidental contact to Duren's (DET) head after Duren loses control of the incoming pass. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed incidental when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Cunningham (DET) impedes Banchero (ORL) by placing his left hand on Banchero's front and arm, which affects Banchero's SQBR after he gathers.
Carter Jr. (ORL) makes incidental contact with Thompson's (DET) leg as both players come together during the rebound.
Banchero (ORL) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Cunningham's (DET) driving shot attempt.

Banchero (ORL) gathers the ball on his left foot and comes to a legal jump stop, allowing him to slide his right foot, establishing his left as his pivot. He then maintains his pivot foot before his upward shooting motion.
Duren (DET) gets drawn in the air and moves into Banchero's (ORL) space, initiating body contact during Banchero's upward shooting motion.
